    <layer level="1" name="Layer 1">
      <focus/>
      <content>Basic terms: Access Control (mediates subject-object interactions via policies), Repository (code/package storage), Subject (requester), Object (resource), RBAC (role-based), ABAC (attribute-based). Quiz: Match terms to definitions.</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="2" name="Layer 2">
      <focus/>
      <content>Relationships: Policies evaluate subject attributes (e.g., role, location), object sensitivity, environment (time, IP). Compare RBAC (static roles) vs. ABAC (dynamic). Diagram: Subject → Policy Engine → Object. Just-in-time example: GitHub teams as RBAC.</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="3" name="Layer 3">
      <focus/>
      <content>Practical steps: GitHub - Create teams/org roles (RBAC), Branch protection rules; GitLab - Groups/projects with custom roles, ABAC via external auth. Best practices: Least privilege, audit logs. Hands-on: Configure protected branches.</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="4" name="Layer 4">
      <focus/>
      <content>Advanced: CI/CD (e.g., GitHub Actions require approvals), Zero-Trust (continuous verification), Supply chain (SLSA framework). Case study: Integrate with OPA for policy-as-code.</content>
    </layer>
  </scaffolding>
